Key Observations

Legacy transactions store the signature data directly inside the transaction input scripts. Because of this, the entire signature contributes to the transaction size.

SegWit transactions move most of the signature data into the witness structure, which is stored separately from the main transaction body.

Although the raw transaction size of SegWit may appear slightly larger in bytes, the virtual size and weight are significantly lower. This means SegWit transactions are cheaper in terms of transaction fees and allow more transactions to fit inside a block.

This demonstrates the scalability benefits introduced by the SegWit upgrade.
